result.name: Il Bel Paese

reviews.text: Cheesy juicy homemade lasagna.. girls were nice and friendly, serving was perfect.. served my mate salad and my lasagna at the same time ... just someone could not resist to had the first bite. Nice sitting area outside to enjoy the sun and atmosphere, though we sat inside the shop and enjoyed the smell of cheese and wine around us. Lovely weekend lunch indeed.
Perfect for a local DB experience.  Daily snack buffet is value for money without compromising on quality.
Everything I had was superb.  Special mention to the pan fried salmon though. Perfectly done!

Never again!!!

I have eaten and loved Italian food all my life and spent a considerable amount of it in Italy primarily Rome. Italians like the French pride themselves on their sauces... bad sauce = bad food to them. I know Italian chefs that would have gone crazy seeing this mess on my plate. Sauce was watery and had no real flavour apart from a very subtle tomato taste, The chicken was overcooked and dry with even my dog turning her nose up until she realised it was all that was on offer 😁.
The garlic bread was also overcooked, seriously how can you overcook garlic bread???
Considering this was the Chefs special I would expect it to be something he/she was proud to serve. If they are proud of serving that they should change career!
Pricing was far too expensive and just compounded a miserable meal for me.
1* is too much but lowest I can give 😟
Great service and food at good price
